      Connection(long carId, java.util.concurrent.LinkedBlockingQueue<IData> controlDataQueue, java.util.concurrent.LinkedBlockingQueue<ControlChangeQueueElement> controlChangeQueue)
      A simple constructor with the minimal set of parameters to instantiate a working subclass of this class.

      The connections that have control over the different control-data-sets cannot be set here and need to be set after instantiation, via Connection.updateControllingDevice(ControlChangeQueueElement) or {link Connection.updateControllingDevice(long, EDataType).

    • Uses of IData in at.ac.tuwien.ict.andropicar.rmcs.data

      Subinterfaces of IData in at.ac.tuwien.ict.andropicar.rmcs.data 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      interface  IControlData
      A general class for all classes used to store control-data.
      Although the class itself does not provide any functionality (does not have attributes or methods), it is necessary to have a common class for the LinkedBlockingQueues that are used to send control-data-sets between the different modules / threads.
      Classes in at.ac.tuwien.ict.andropicar.rmcs.data that implement IData 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  CameraControlData
      Contains one set of values for controlling the RMCSs camera rotation.

      Contains one set of values of the RMCSs distance-sensors.
      class  DriveControlData
      Contains one set of values for controlling the RMCSs drive (acceleration/velocity and steering).
      class  LightControlData
      Contains one set of values for controlling the RMCSs lights (front / back, winkers).
